c. I need to ensure that the `-XX` arguments are properly recognized by the launcher. There’s a lot to consider, and it’s essential to get the configuration right for efficient testing!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering image support issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking there might be a problem with native image support for `ProcessHandle`. It seems unlikely that it could spawn in JVM tests. I need to avoid using `@TempDir` imports and instead, maybe utilize `Files.createTempDirectory` and ensure it gets deleted afterward. Also, what if the `script` isn’t installed or interactive? In that case, I should use `isPseudoTerminalLauncherAvailable`. If it’s not, then I can create an assertion like `assertThat(...).as(...).isTrue()`. I wonder if this failing issue is specific to Mac while working in CI Linux.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_C8ggdNQkxagIWtDxq2oKLShe|fc_0c0195d7c217b20c016a2508e013b08190a26380650618b628", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/AnsiOutputTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.Console;\nimport java.util.Locale;\n", "newText": "import java.io.Console;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.time.Duration;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Locale;\nimport java.util.Optional;\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void alwaysEncodesAnsiElements() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void nativeExecutableCanDetectAnsiWhenLaunchedWithPseudoTerminal() throws Exception {\n        Optional<List<String>> command = currentNativeTestCommand();\n        if (command.isPresent() && System.getenv(\"ANSI_OUTPUT_PTY_CHILD\") == null && isPseudoTerminalLauncherAvailable()) {\n            Path xmlOutputDir = Files.createTempDirectory(\"ansi-output-native-child-\");\n            List<String> childCommand = withChildXmlOutput(command.get(), xmlOutputDir);\n            Process process = new ProcessBuilder(\"script\", \"-q\", \"-e\", \"-c\", shellCommand(childCommand), \"/dev/null\")\n                .redirectErrorStream(true)\n                .start();\n            assertThat(process.waitFor(Duration.ofSeconds(55).toMillis(), TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS)).isTrue();\n            assertThat(process.exitValue()).isZero();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void alwaysEncodesAnsiElements() {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static boolean isWindows() {\n        return System.getProperty(\"os.name\").toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH).contains(\"win\");\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static Optional<List<String>> currentNativeTestCommand() {\n        Optional<String> command = ProcessHandle.current().info().command();\n        if (command.isEmpty() || isJavaLauncher(command.get())) {\n            return Optional.empty();\n        }\n        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();\n        result.add(command.get());\n        ProcessHandle.current().info().arguments().ifPresent((arguments) -> result.addAll(Arrays.asList(arguments)));\n        return Optional.of(result);\n    }\n\n    private static boolean isJavaLauncher(String command) {\n        String name = Path.of(command).getFileName().toString().toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH);\n        return name.equals(\"java\") || name.equals(\"java.exe\");\n    }\n\n    private static boolean isPseudoTerminalLauncherAvailable() {\n        try {\n            Process process = new ProcessBuilder(\"script\", \"--version\").redirectErrorStream(true).start();\n            return process.waitFor(Duration.ofSeconds(5).toMillis(), TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS) && process.exitValue() == 0;\n        }\n        catch (IOException ex) {\n            return false;\n        }\n        catch (InterruptedException ex) {\n            Thread.currentThread().interrupt();\n            return false;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static List<String> withChildXmlOutput(List<String> command, Path xmlOutputDir) {\n        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();\n        for (int i = 0; i < command.size(); i++) {\n            String argument = command.get(i);\n            if (\"--xml-output-dir\".equals(argument)) {\n                i++;\n            }\n            else {\n                result.add(argument);\n            }\n        }\n        result.add(\"--xml-output-dir\");\n        result.add(xmlOutputDir.toString());\n        return result;\n    }\n\n    private static String shellCommand(List<String> command) {\n        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();\n        for (String argument : command) {\n            if (!result.isEmpty()) {\n                result.append(' ');\n            }\n            result.append('\\'').append(argument.replace(\"'\", \"'\\\\''\")).append('\\'');\n        }\n        return result.toString();\n    }\n\n    private static boolean isWindows() {\n        return System.getProperty(\"os.name\").toLowerCase(Locale.ENGLISH).contains(\"win\");\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 294, "output": 2359, "cacheRead": 43520, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46173, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780811964176, "responseId": "resp_0c0195d7c217b20c016a2508bcd0e08190bbcfd1d81121d3df"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_C8ggdNQkxagIWtDxq2oKLShe|fc_0c0195d7c217b20c016a2508e013b08190a26380650618b628", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 3 block(s) in tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/4.0.6/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/AnsiOutputTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n   6  */\n   7 package org_springframework_boot.spring_boot;\n   8 \n   9 import java.io.Console;\n+ 10 import java.io.IOException;\n+ 11 import 